# Semgrep ignore rules for the VoiceFlow monorepo.
#
# Anything in this file is excluded from `semgrep ci` scans. Inline rule-level
# suppressions live next to the offending code as `# nosemgrep: <rule-id>`.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Archived / legacy code paths.
# These directories hold one-off training scripts, ad-hoc ONNX exporters and
# experimental notebooks that predate the production refactor. They are NOT
# shipped to production (excluded from Docker images, not imported by the
# runtime) and should not gate CI.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
voiceflow-ml/archive/
voiceflow-ml/notebooks/archive_experiments/
voiceflow-ml/notebooks/archive_misaligned/

# Generated artefacts (shouldn't normally be checked in but are a safety net).
voiceflow-ml/htmlcov/
voiceflow-ml/.coverage
voiceflow-ml/coverage.xml
voiceflow-inference/target/

# Test fixtures (binary or autogenerated audio blobs).
voiceflow-ml/tests/fixtures/

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Terraform modules with documented architectural opt-outs.
#
# These three files contain resources whose Semgrep findings are intentional
# and have been reviewed in code (see the comment block above each resource).
#   * ecr/main.tf            — image_tag_mutability is opt-in via variable so
#                              the dev environment can be MUTABLE while prod
#                              is hard-pinned IMMUTABLE.
#   * networking/main.tf     — public subnets must auto-assign IPv4s for the
#                              ALB + NAT to work; workloads live in private.
#   * ecs/main.tf            — has a dev-only HTTP fallback listener that is
#                              count = 0 in every TLS-enabled environment.
#
# Inline `# nosemgrep` comments are unreliable for Terraform because Semgrep
# matches at the resource-block level. Excluding the file is the documented
# escape hatch (see https://semgrep.dev/docs/ignoring-files-folders-code).
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
infra/modules/ecr/main.tf
infra/modules/networking/main.tf
infra/modules/ecs/main.tf
